no immediate comment on the board decision she said the company 
operates four 10000ton ships each carrying 950 to 1100 
passengers on cruises out of miami 
in the last decade the board has investigated five major fires 
aboard cruise vessels three of them on sea escape ships one in 
1984 killed one passenger and one crew member scores of people have 
been injured mostly from smoke inhalation 
no other deaths have been reported in accidents aboard 
americanoperated cruise ships but a cuban ship captain and two 
sailors were killed when the usowned celebration cut their 
freighter in half feb 10 
the board is seeking court orders to force witnesses to give 
