started with an oil leak it said fuel pipe packing seals and 
deflector sleeves that would have prevented the oil from being 
ignited were deteriorated and had not been replaced 
im afraid this ship was being managed more like a night club 
than a vessel said board member burnett who led the 
investigation into the fire 
the ship which was towed to miami after the fire was put out 
has since been repaired and is back in operation 
