the accounting firms deloitte haskins amp sells and touche ross amp 
co have agreed in principle to join forces while two larger big 
eight firms confirmed that they had entered into merger negotiations 
subject to the approval of partners at deloitte and touche ross 
the combined company would have worldwide revenue exceeding 4 
billion and employ over 65000 people in 101 countries it will be 
known as deloitte amp touche in the united states the firms said in a 
statement thursday 
separately arthur andersen amp co and price waterhouse confirmed 
reports that they had begun talks about a possible merger of their 
worldwide operations a confidentiality agreement will be in effect 
for the next 60 days while the proposition is being explored 
an andersenwaterhouse merger would create the worlds largest 
accounting firm reaping 5 billion a year in worldwide revenue and 
27 billion in us revenue 
the merger wave among the big eight firms began weeks ago with 
the announcement that ernst amp whinney and arthur young amp co agreed 
to combine their operations to create an accounting firm with 
worldwide revenue of 42 billion and domestic revenue of 2 billion 
although deloitte and touche ross are the smallest of the 
socalled big eight firms they have posted the most rapid growth in 
recent years between 1985 and 1988 their individual worldwide 
revenue jumped more than 88 percent according to bowmans 
accounting report an industry publication 
last year their worldwide growth averaged 26 percent compared 
with an average of 22 percent for the other big eight firms 
deloitte and touche ross noted their desire to serve 
multinational companies in todays global economy as a primary 
reason for the merger 
edward a kangas managing partner and chief executive of touche 
ross issued a statement saying a strong european capability is 
vital to serving our clients needs as the economic unification of 
europe in 1992 approaches 
deloitte chairman and chief executive officer j michael cook 
also pointed to the economic growth of the pacific rim as a need for 
a strengthened presence in asia the combined firm will draw on the 
expertise of the japanese audit firm tohmatsu awoki amp sanwa a 
member of the touche ross international organization 
worldwide the firm will be known as deloitte ross tohmatsu 
international 
kangas and cook will serve as chief executives of the 
international organization and the us firm respectively kangas 
also will serve as a managing partner of the us firm 
experts generally agreed that the merger makes sense 
particularly because the accounting industry has become increasingly 
specialized 
among deloittes audit clients are general motors 
kimberlyclark monsanto and procter amp gamble said arthur bowman 
publisher of the atlantabased bowmans accounting report 
touche rosss audit clients include american motors chrysler 
litton industries and pillsbury he said 
deloitte also displays its strength in the mergers and 
acquisitions arena bowman said the firm is a favorite of kohlberg 
kravis roberts amp co the powerful new york investment firm 
kkr tapped deloitte to perform a number of accountingrelated 
services for its record 25 billion buyout of rjr nabisco as well as 
other targets including safeway and beatrice 
in a joint statement price waterhouse chairman joseph e connor 
and arthur andersen chief executive lawrence e weinbach said the 
the firms are seeking to benefit from the globalization of world 
economies accelerating technological changes and demand for new 
services and investments 
these developments are creating a demand for increased 
worldwide professional and financial resources which to serve 
clients needs their statement read 
arthur andersen is the secondlargest us accounting firm while 
price waterhouse ranks fifth 
together the two firms would audit almost 40 percent of the 
fortune 500 which could lead to federal trade commission concerns 
about a competitive imbalance bowman said 
the firms did not comment on whether any employees would be let 
go but observers suspect support staff will be cut 
they will definitely have to let people go at the support 
level the nonprofessional staffs bowman said and there will 
be some fallout at the partner level you dont need two partners in 
charge of the same little area 
but fees are unlikely to head lower despite savings from 
consolidation 
they cant lower the hourly rates that theyre charging so the 
only thing they can save on is administrative and certain overhead 
costs to help the bottom line said one accountant at a 
secondtier firm who asked not to be named 
