<TEXT>
boeing co engineers on thursday were trying to 
determine why an aging united airlines 727 developed a 20inch crack 
in a part of its fuselage 
the split was in the same general area as the rupture in an aloha 
airlines 737 that lost part of its roof over hawaii last year 
however both boeing and the federal aviation administration said 
the cracking appeared entirely different from that in the aloha 
plane 
this is a unique situation said faa spokesman david duff in 
